  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0baf \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0baa\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bb4\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Departmental officials will be invited to the COPE committee to examine fuel price hike",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Public Utilities Commission Chairman Janaka Ratnayake mentioned that petrol and diesel can be sold at 250 rupees.",
        "People have paid more attention to this issue. Professor Saritha Herath, chairman of the COPE Committee, said that officials of the Electricity Department and Power, Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka will be invited to the COPE committee in the coming days to investigate the fuel price hike.",
        "The COPE committee met yesterday to review the audit report for the year 2018 and 2019 and the current performance of the Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka.",
        "After a thorough study of fuel procurement and taxation, it was found that fuel can be dispensed at Rs.250.",
        "Janaka Ratnayake said that it is his personal opinion that one liter of petrol and diesel can be sold for less than 250 rupees.",
        "Public Utilities Commission chairman's comments on fuel prices are serious. People have paid more attention to this issue.",
        "Officials of the Ministry of Power and Electricity and Public Utilities Commission have been invited to the CoP committee in the coming days.",
        "Chairman of Public Utility Commission Janaka Ratnayake told the committee that it was observed that there has been a mistake in the determination of fuel prices.",
        "The Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation distributes fuel to the Electricity Board. The tariff revision proposed by the Power Minister has not been implemented due to proper procedures.",
        "Minister Mahinda Amaraweera questioned whether the tariff amendment was prepared by the minister or the officers of the ministry.",
        "I don't know that, the Minister has uploaded it on Twitter page.",
        "The difference between import and duty is Rs 150-200. The total import cost for diesel is estimated at Rs 174.",
        "The Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission mentioned that the cost of import of fuel per liter will not increase beyond 350 rupees."
      ],
